column5: Well the first 2013 ice fishing trip was great. The sun was out warn all day, awesome ice and oh yah... a few 14 inch slabers
Very nice...where were you at? We were on Chemong today but only managed couple dink perch and a little rocky.
Thanks it wasn't my spot or my lake so I am sworn to secrecy.
Thats the thing about good crappie spots.....no one will ever tell you and if you find a spot on your own you have to keep it a secret!!......nice fish!!

Its part of the code. You want to find it you gotta get out there. If I find a spot I'll take people there blindfolded with a cavity search for gps's. Haha  I was trying to get a few pics of them to show the size...  The sink shot...    And the traditional full size dinner plate shot...
Nicely done. We were at our Crappie spot today and we were rewarded for the third time in 3 trips. Can you say Honey Hole???
Those are the nicest crappie I've ever seen.  Good job!
Those are some slabs Vince; not much is tastier than a good ol' crappie kill! Darc

Oh yah, I hear you on that one. I love crappie. One of the best eating fish around. These are PB's for me by about 2 inches. I haven't seen any bigger caught in person before. I have seen pictures of some hogs and heard stories of 16 inchers... I'll be on the prowl for bigger this season. 16 inch's and I might get it mounted.
Nice slabs man!!  My crappie season is over.   But seeing those big boys.... Make me want to head back out!
